<section class="fractal-nature">
    <h2>The Fractal Nature of Reality</h2>
    
    <div class="fractal-container">
        <div class="sierpinski-triangle">
            <div class="triangle t1"></div>
            <div class="triangle t2"></div>
            <div class="triangle t3"></div>
            <div class="triangle t4"></div>
            <div class="triangle t5"></div>
            <div class="triangle t6"></div>
            <div class="triangle t7"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="fractal-explanation">
        <p>
            The self-similar patterns found in nature, from quantum fluctuations to cosmic 
            structures, suggest an underlying unity and interconnectedness in reality. 
            This fractal nature of existence bridges the microscopic and macroscopic, 
            the physical and the philosophical.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    .fractal-nature {
        margin: 4rem 0;
        padding: 2rem;
        background: rgba(var(--accent-dark), 0.2);
        border-radius: 12px;
        text-align: center;
    }

    h2 {
        color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .fractal-container {
        height: 400px;
        margin: 2rem 0;
        position: relative;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
    }

    .sierpinski-triangle {
        width: 300px;
        height: 260px;
        position: relative;
    }

    .triangle {
        position: absolute;
        border-left: 25px solid transparent;
        border-right: 25px solid transparent;
        border-bottom: 43.3px solid rgb(var(--accent-light));
        opacity: 0;
        animation: appear 0.5s forwards;
    }

    .t1 {
        top: 0;
        left: 125px;
        animation-delay: 0s;
    }

    .t2 {
        top: 43.3px;
        left: 100px;
        animation-delay: 0.5s;
    }

    .t3 {
        top: 43.3px;
        left: 150px;
        animation-delay: 1s;
    }

    .t4 {
        top: 86.6px;
        left: 75px;
        animation-delay: 1.5s;
    }

    .t5 {
        top: 86.6px;
        left: 125px;
        animation-delay: 2s;
    }

    .t6 {
        top: 86.6px;
        left: 175px;
        animation-delay: 2.5s;
    }

    .t7 {
        top: 129.9px;
        left: 125px;
        animation-delay: 3s;
    }

    .fractal-explanation {
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 2rem auto;
    }

    @keyframes appear {
        from {
            opacity: 0;
            transform: scale(0) rotate(180deg);
        }
        to {
            opacity: 1;
            transform: scale(1) rotate(0deg);
        }
    }
</style>